 color=#C54400>Author</font></td><td valign=top background=http://members.aol.com/greyspiral/EQ/testbg.gif class=headings><font color=#C54400>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ada07e><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ukyalynn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kya Lynn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#c54400>(10/4/00 4:10:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Information departed</span><hr size=1> &quot;Ahh...the fair and lovely Kygero. My favorite little wood elf has come at last to see me. I trust your journey to our evil city was a safe and non eventful one?&quot; Xaithan's quite voice echoed in the room to which we met, unconciously giving it a dangerous undertone. Always fearing for my life when coming to this foul city i watched my back and had ready many battle spells and escape spells on the top of my mind. &quot;Yes Dark One, it was an uneventful trip but i pray let us be hasty. There is so much i need to know and very little in the way of time to prepare.&quot; I bowed my head in honor of his Vileness and again wondered  as i did when speaking to him of what i was doing with this evil creature. Tunare forgive and protect me.<br>
&quot;Well then let us start soon, but please, let us share in a glass of Elvin wine whilst we talk. I believe it is your favorite drink....right?&quot; he asked with that evil grin painted across his face. Xaithan motioned towards the door and a beautiful female drow walked into the room carrying a tray of wine, bread and cheese. She set the tray down on the large cherry stained table. First she poured Xaithan a glass and then turned to me. As she did so, her eyes locked onto mine and both our faces flushed with color. There was an odd feeling passing through my body and i could see the same affect happening to her. I looked over to Xaithan and noticed that he was enjoying all this a little more than he should. What on Norrath could this be all about? When she was finished seeing to our needs, her head turned my way and she shot me an evil look that seemed to have daggers of death behind it.<br>
&quot;Thank you Aingel, you are dismissed to your studies again and see to our privacy. No interruptions, do you understand?<br>
&quot;Yes Master Xaithan, it will be done. Aingel said as she bowed to him and backed out of the room giving me one last icy glare.<br>
Not being able to hold back i asked, &quot;Who was that your evilness?&quot; He looked to me and casually responded with a wave of his hand, &quot;That is just a new apprentice i have taken on, nothing more. But as you can see, she doesn't share my pleasure in entertaining one such as yourself. She will one day understand, like me, that it is neccesary to have light in the world as well as the dark. We are but two sides of the same coin. Of course i'm sure you know that already. Think of her no more and let us get to the reasoning of your being here. The Plague Bringers are attempting to destroy your precious guild and bring about the dishonor of Tunare.&quot; Choosing my words carefully, i began.<br>
&quot;Do you have any idea why this Iszabelle is wanting to destroy my brothers and sisters of the Bronze Dragons? We know that she has taken Caddil prisoner and is getting Phyllis from another dark elf here in the city. She also gave Molina the plague and has attempted to recruit others from our guild to her own evil purposes. There doesn't seem to be any connection with her and our guild, so why do this? It makes no sense to me.&quot; i asked.<br>
Xaithan looked at me for a long moment before answering. &quot;Kygero, does there need to be a reason? As you said yourself, we are ruled by chaos and such being the case, we do things chaotically and without reason. Fortunately for you i anticipated this visit and gathered some information from the spirits of the dead, from my, what do you call it....forbidden arts? Yes that is how i came up with some of the answers you seek. Are you still interested in learning all you can knowing that?&quot; he smiled that crooked smile again. Damn him for enjoying all this!<br>
Pondering for only a second on the matter, i answered him, &quot;Of course i still want to know. I did not ask you to find the answers that way and so i am clean of your sins, but this IS most important! Tunares children are in danger! And they are my family and will do anything for them!&quot; As i said this last, it dawned on me that i was playing right into his little mind game and needed to control myself. Gaining my composure, i looked over to Xaithan steadily. He raised his glass and took another drink before commencing to speak again.<br>
&quot;I was able to ascertain that Iszabelle has it in for your Paladin sister Phyllis more than any other in your guild. You see, she is the daughter of a man named Connor. I couldn't gather why Iszabelle hates Phyllis's bloodline, but i assume that this Connor fellow killed Iszablle's parents or other family members a long time ago. Well that makes sense to me, does it not? Regardless, since Phyllis is a part of the Fellowship, that is why Iszabelle wants to annihilate you all. She wants to kill any that Phyllis cares for and all that care for Phyllis. Mind you i think this to be a tall order, but it seems she started the whole ordeal in an ingenious fashion. It looks to me that she holds the upper hand at this time.&quot; taking a breath he continued. &quot;Also she has a plan with Farvak to slowly drive your dear guild sister Katreena insane. Iszabelle hopes to turn Katreena against the BDF by pushing a wedge there using Caddil. And Farvak wants her to bare his unholy child to maybe have control of their Innoruuk blessed relationship? I'm not sure of his reasoning. Here i thought i had a sick mind...this Farvak is twisted even beyond that of some of my own associates. I could almost admire him if he weren't so sloppy and such a fool.&quot; he replied.<br>
&quot;That is about all i could come up with from the dead. They are not a cooperative bunch i'm afraid.&quot; again that smile.<br>
Getting weary of staying here any longer in the hands of evil, i decided it was time to leave.<br>
&quot;Ok then, i have gotten what i've come for and now must report. There are things to be done and Lord Rashek must be told all this. I'm sure he will come up with something. Thank you again Druidsbane, and may Tunare forgive and embrace you.&quot; i dared to say.<br>
His smile faded upon my utterance of Tunare and his forgiveness. Xaithan would have killed anyone else in an instant for saying such a thing to him. Instead his smile returned and he obviously wasn't finished with me. &quot;One other thing before you depart...she has decided upon her next prey.&quot; He paused here for a long time, taking a drink of his wine again, and slicing off a piece of the bread and cheese to slowly consume. Being respectful of him, i waited patiently. Xaithan continued to chew his food slowly and stare at me as if this were a game. A minute passed then two....as the time drifted into the past, my patience wore thin. Finally i could take no more of this.<br>
&quot;Damn it Xaithan, stop this madness and tell me!!&quot;<br>
He opened his mouth and softly spoke the name, &quot;Gorsha.&quot; That was all he had to say. My heart froze and a rage began to build inside me. How dare that wicked beast Iszabelle! I looked all around the room as if there was an answer there to my dilema. Calmly Xaithan said, &quot;I figured that would have an affect on you.&quot; I turned my head back to him and quickly settled, not wanting to give him the advantage over me and my feelings. That could be a dangerous thing with this evil being.<br>
I had to go find Gorsha. If i could get to him before Iszabelle, then maybe we could get a small advantage ourselves. And if she showed her face then i would end her evil plans myself with her death! That i promised.<br>
&quot;I must take my leave now Xaithan. As always your cooperation is greatly appreciated. I am in debt to you for this.&quot; My chair skidded across the earthen ground as i pushed away from the table and stood.<br>
&quot;Kygero, understand this, with the invaluable info i have departed to you here...we are now even by my considerations of my life debt that was yours. From this day on, i owe you just as you owe me....Nothing!! Now be gone from here fair druid.&quot; With that he turned his back to me in dismissal.<br>
At least i knew where he and i stood. I bowed to him and began to call upon my Tunare given powers to take me far from here. The rip in space appeared in front of me ready to take me to West Commons. As per usual of my nature, i couldn't help but to look back at Xaithan one last time. He was there looking back at me...was that a look of sorrow? Not likely coming from him, i must've misread him.<br>
&quot;We will see each other again soon Kygero, Innoruuk willing!&quot; and i stepped through the portal to feel the cold comfort of the dark surround me. Gorsha, where are you?<br>
<br>
Kygero Keibugami<br>
Druid of the 40th leaf<br>
