<br>
   When he got up to leave I quickly left to follow him.  My intention was to ask him if I could come with him, but knew that he would say no.  I longed to be anywhere but in High Keep.  To just be doing something other than long days and nights keeping vigilance over Khaldron. I desired to be in green meadows and under trees,  High Keep offered none of this.<br>
<br>
   When I caught up with him, I  did suggest that he take Slaor just for back up. Maybe find Calicer or Gorsha, I hadn't heard from either of them in a long time. Banlean said he would keep an eye out for both men. <br>
<br>
    I was walking back to my room when a dark figure stepped from the shadows.  He spoke in a whisper &quot;You must come with me now, I have news of Caddil&quot;.<br>
<br>
    I looked at him and questioned &quot;Your not a member of the Bronze Dragon Fellowship, how did you get in here?&quot;  <br>
<br>
    He repeated &quot;Do you want to save your husband, Kat, or not?  If so, then come with me now.&quot;  I quickly followed him my heart racing.  Quickly down one passage and then another, I had not ventured here and followed him onward. Only stopping briefly to find a secret passageway out of the Keep.<br>
<br>
    I continued behind this stranger eager to hear of the promised news of Caddil.   It was when we had cleared Highhold pass and were well into Kithicor Forest that I said  &quot;Stop now, please tell me now Is he alive?&quot; This Barbarian spoke as he glanced back over his  shoulder  &quot;Yes, but not much time to waste follow me now if we are to save him&quot;.  I dare not stop in the Woods here I knew to well the dark evil that ruled this place.  Following behind him I realized I had no weapon, no armor, not even my spell book.  I only questioned this for a moment and then dismissed it quickly as I was now more concerned that Caddil may be dying somewhere.  I was holding onto the ring at my neck  praying to Mother Tunare under my breath as we moved onward.  <br>
<br>
     My legs ached from running, my heart pounding hard in my chest, I was breathing hard, my side aching from trying to keep up with this man.  We finally stopped at a group of empty huts just outside the entrance to Nektulos Forest when he turned and looked down at me &quot;Are you ready to see your love?&quot;  I quickly moved from one hut to the next hoping to find Caddil there. The barbarian stepping close behind me  <br>
<br>
     He then smiled evilly, casting root on me so that my feet sank into the ground, he then stepped aside.  Farvak came from behind him laughing with this man. &quot;Still gullible and trusting as ever aren't you Kat&quot;  Farvak said. Then turned and asked &quot;She came eagerly did she not, Ragingwolf?&quot; <br>
<br>
     &quot;Aye, she almost turned back, but her blind love ensured that she would come.  Praying all the way.&quot; he replied chuckling. &quot;The sweet thing is no one saw us leave.&quot; <br>
<br>
     &quot;Ah, very good Raging, I owe you for this one&quot; Farvak answered pleased with himself.  <p>Katreena Wanderheart 40th Leaf Master Brewer <br>
<a
herf=http://members.home.net/soyouthinkiam/eq/Kat/images/"target="web"><img src="http://members.home.net/soyouthinkiam/eq/Kat/images/KatReflectSig.gif" border="0"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ada07e><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ukatreena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katreena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight, Order of Talon</span><br>  Posts: 242<br> <font color=#c54400>(10/22/00 7:48:04 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/soyouthinkiam/eq/Kat/images/Katpix.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>    In the Service of Mother Tunare</span><hr size=1> I found myself once again under Farvak's demented control.  Raging Wolf had brought the chains and shackles that would bind me to Farvak  for now.  There was little hope of escape.<br>
<br>
Farvak took every opportunity to shame me and my belief in Mother Tunare.  As we walked into Nektkous Forest, he would jerk the chains tripping me so that soon my knees where bloody my neck and wrists were bruised.  I had been stripped of most of my garments and what I had on was torn and dirty now as I was paraded in front of those who worshiped the Evil and Dark Gods.<br>
<br>
The children through stones and sticks at me, there where those that spat on me, the males of this ungodly group would grope my body, the women jeered.  I heard laughter and vile names cursed at me from every corner of this forest before we stopped to camp.  <br>
<br>
Farvak tossed food on the ground my way, I'm sure it was wolf meat, I didn't eat disgusted by the smell.  To drink Farvak had poured water on the ground making a small muddy puddle. Farvak laughed and said &quot;Yes, drink like the dog you are.  You will have many such lessons before I am through with you. At last my time has come to finish the job I started so many years ago in Kithicor.&quot;<br>
<br>
 There was no soft grass to sleep in, No warm blankets to cover myself with. My body dirty, aching and cold I curled up and let my mind call out to anyone who would help. I couldn't reach out for somehow Farvak had a spell over me so that this one last hope was crushed as well.  I was so tired, but only dozed on and off keeping my eyes of Farvak all the while.  I knew what was in store for me now no mercy would be shown to me here, my spirit would be crushed, my body made to serve, my mind lost in madness.  <br>
<br>
In the Morning I was offered more spoiled meat and muddy water.  Then ordered  to carry the heavy packs that Farvak had had his pet carry the night before.  He again jerked my chains if I slowed.  If he felt I resisted he would then pull so that I fell to the ground, saying &quot;You must learn your place now Kat, your my pet.   I must teach you who is master here I will control all that you are and do from now on.  If you do not please me I will take you to the guards or worse yet to the Hell of Sciences where they will make what I do to you look like loving touches&quot;.       <br>
<br>
Rumors had spread that Hell of Sciences was beyond demented and tortured but truly Hell on Norrath.  I winced at the thought of my most horrid imaginings and knew that they were but shadows of what would happen to me there.<br>
<br>
Farvak said finally &quot;Rule 1:  I am your Master you are never to look at me directly ever again. Rule 2: If I tell you to do something you must do it without hesitation.  Rule 3: You will worship My God and denounce yours.  Rule 4: You will never escape me. Don't attempted it.  Rule 5: never speak to me unless I give you permission.  Rule 6: You will always show me that you totally bend  to all my wishes.  You will no longer be allowed the high and heady attitude you have had towards the Dark Eleven races.  You are beneath us and you are unworthy to even be among us.  The punishment for breaking any of these rules will be severe.  Do I make myself clear!.<br>
  <br>
  I dared not answer so I keeping my head bowed shook my head, yes. I thought to myself for now I would agree but in my heart I would never denounce Mother Tunare.  The rest I could accept with some grief.  I knew I would not be allowed to die that would be to easy for me and knew Farvak would never allow such a luxury. <br>
<br>
Farvak entered the house and was greeted with warm loving embraces, words of kindness and smiling faces.  Those same faces turned when he pulled my chains and brought<br>
 me into their view.  Those same faces turned cold and evil as their eyes looked me up and down.  A voice from one of them said &quot;Get that filthy creature out of my House.!&quot;  <br>
<br>
&quot;Ah yes, she is vile and beautiful in her hate but you are right we must not treat her as an equal take her and leave her with the  animals to be slaughtered maybe she will find comfort there&quot;.  Farvak's laugh was his order.  <br>
<br>
I was taken to a barn like hut and left there my chains fastened to the wall by a woman servant. She peered at me her eyes widened for only a second then she left. The stench of death was everywhere here.  There were others here of Mother Tunare's a couple of wolves and a great black bear they all seemed to know their fate.<br>
<br>
  I was praying to Mother  Tunare when Farvak walked in looked disgustedly at me.  He spoke &quot;You disappoint me Katreena you have been keeping a secret from me.  My servant has told me you are with child.  Well now I can't have you giving life to anything that would represent love, and especially a child that was conceived in your weak form of love&quot;<br>
<br>
 He sat down and laid my head on his lap then  held my head and poured a bitter potion in my mouth and said &quot;drink&quot;.  I spat it at him, he laughed.  Then he held my nose and waited till I could hold my breath no longer then slowly poured the potion down my throat. &quot;There now this will be better for me as you will feel the life in you die and it will bring Me more passion from you.  Yes,&quot; he seemed to be speaking to himself.  I lay there in the straw and dirt feeling Caddil's and my Child dying inside.<br>
<br>
 &quot;Oh how I want the passion you let go on the Shadow Knight in Befallen those many years ago.  It was then that my desire for  you became consuming.  Your rage, you hate were divine.  Will you Love me so?.  I have had 4 wives now and each could not match the hate or rage you so lovingly showed that night.  The one I have now will be delightful tonight in her jealousy but it will still not match your rage&quot;.  He said almost wishingly.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh look your child is dying&quot; He smiled and kissed away the tears that had crept out of my eyes and rolled down my cheeks. &quot;How delightful this is&quot;  His hand found my breast his fingers found my nipple and he twisted it bringing a wince of pain to my face.  &quot;Oh you are so controlled right now but you will soon let your Rage and Hate free on me.  You know that love and hate are 2 sides of the same coin and your Hate for me is Love.&quot; <br>
<br>
It was then in this very moment I knew what Mother Tunare's message to me was so many years ago. &quot;Show it Love&quot;.  Ah the copper dropped Yes only love would destroy Farvak and the Plaguebringers.  This was the reason why she wanted me trained in the way of the Druid I only hoped that I would be strong enough.  <br>
<br>
Farvak smiled &quot;I am very eager to feel your rage and hate so starting tomorrow we will begin again.  I must help you to lose that control you seem to have over  your rage&quot;.  He again twisted my nipple in his fingers bringing pain to my body and a wince to my face. <br>
<br>
He left me there in all of my sorrow, but I was also comforted by Mother Tunare herself as she blessed me with a vision of Caddil and our Child lovingly together. She then whispered &quot;You will join them and your love will heal all of your wounds&quot;.<br>
<br>
I heard the straw stir and looked quickly around there to my surprise was Kygero.&quot; It is I sis. I have come to help you escape&quot; she whispered as she unlocked the chains.<br>
<br>
  &quot;No!&quot; I quickly replied &quot;I will not be leaving yet&quot;. In the shadows and light I saw her eyes grow big &quot;What, come now don't be a fool you need to leave now&quot; urgency was in her voice now.<br>
  <br>
&quot;Kygero thank you for your help but Mother Tunare has given me a great task to do here. The Plaguebringers must be destroyed and this is where she has placed me to do the most good&quot; I answered firmly. <br>
<br>
 Kygero looked into my eyes and bowed &quot;Oh sister&quot; she said sadly understanding now.  &quot;Is there anything that I may do to assist you, Kat.?&quot;  &quot;Yes, please tell Rashek the Child is dead&quot;. She looked at me startled and then tears filled her eyes as she understood all to clearly what I had said. &quot;Oh no, not Caddil's and yours&quot;  &quot;Yes&quot; I replied.  She hugged me as we both mourned the loss of an innocent life. &quot; This battle has been hard on you Kat. Yet your strength and Love for Mother Tunare has always shown through&quot; <br>
<br>
 &quot;Now if you would take Caddil's ring and put it with my stuff till I return. Then take Caddil&quot;s Armor and give it to his sister Luner she will understand as well.  Then if you would, I know this is asking much of you, bring me my spell book.  That is all I will need here.  I hope to have some information that will help the Bronze Dragons to defeat the Plaguebringers next time I see you.  Oh, that reminds me do tell Rashek that my Orders supersede his as they come from Mother Tunare, Herself. To send no rescue at this time I will be keeping Farvak very busy for a while this may gain him some time&quot; <br>
<br>
She hugged me one last time fastened the chains back around my wrist.  She was then at the door quickly with just one last look back and was gone.  Alone again I let my sorrow consume me.   <br>
<br>
