Now that i was leaving the small building that Katreena was being held in, it almost made me sick to think of not taking her out of Fravak's dirty little hands. But armed with confidence in my sister and her decision to stay, it was time to do as she bid and get her spell book for her. At least i was able to give her some food stuffs and fresh water to hide for her consumption. Now to go and break the news to our fellow guild members of the going on's of Kat and her child that will never see the light of Norrath. She is so strong to stay in the face of such adversity. Mother Tunare protect her, enough of your children have suffered at the hands of these wretched creatures, the Plague Bringers! And may Katreena get the last laugh on Fravak. I only hope there is enough of him left when she is done for me to play with!<br>
Running to the tree that was hiding Mythias, i stopped just short of him as a gaurd was nearing. I hid and readied a battle spell, fortunately he did not see me or Mythias and continued on his way. As i came up to my reptilian friend, he had an odd look about him and he asked,&quot;Where isss your guild sssissster, Katreena?&quot; he was obviously thinking the worst. &quot;She has decided to stay where she is for now and do what she can here to delay Fravak.&quot;, i replied.<br>
&quot;What? You are kidding right? You ssshould go back and convinccce her to come away from thisss placcce now! And if ssshe doesssn't come, then we can take her forcccefully for her own good. Ssshe will underssstand when her health returnsss and ssshe isss in her right mind.&quot; <br>
A rage began to build in me for being in such a predicament and the blood in me began to boil. My face became flushed and i snapped at Mythias for no reason.&quot;NO damn it!! Katreena has made her decision, and as much as i hate to, we must leave her to her designs. She is strong willed and would never forgive me, besides Mother Tunare is watching over her.&quot; i paused and regained control of my feelings. &quot;Please forgive me good friend, i am merely worried for her safety and allowed a bit of weakness to show. You are the best for helping us and i had no reason to take it out on you.&quot;<br>
Mythias smiled, bareing his sharp teeth, which tended to give him a menacing look more than a friendly one, but i knew him and it was good to see him do it. &quot;No worriesss Kygero, i do underssstand. You are good to your guild sssissster and i can sssee that you love her very much. We ssshall leave her where ssshe isss for now. Ssso what ssshall we do in the mean time?&quot;<br>
I thought for only a second, then formed a plan in my head quickly. &quot;Mythias, i have to ask you to stay here and continue you vigilant watch over her while i retrieve her spell book and give Rashek Caddil's wedding ring. I promise to return hastely as it will not take to long to do these things. I will bind right here so as to make my trip even quicker. If you do not wish to stay and feel it too angerous then know that i understand whole heartedly.&quot;<br>
