&quot;It is the least we can do Kat. Mythias will contact me quickly if you need help, i will come on the winds and am bound just outside the clearing where he stands gaurd. So scream if you need us and we will come!!&quot; I hugged her tightly and kissed her cheek then camoed myself again. &quot;Good Fortune and may Tunare's light shine upon your head while in this dark time!&quot; Bowing even though she could not see me i took my leave from the shack.<br>
&quot;You watch your back as well Kygero!&quot; Katreena's voice followed me out as i went to where Mythias was watching. The times were getting harder by the sun and moon cycle. These Plague Bringers must feel the cure to there diseased life essences and soon!! While i was discussing things with Mythias, we were unaware of another presence watching from the shadows. The female dark elf apprentice of Xaithan, Aingel, watched us and relayed information to her dark master. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ada07e><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ukatreena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katreena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight, Order of Talon</span><br>  Posts: 266<br> <font color=#c54400>(11/2/00 6:40:40 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/soyouthinkiam/eq/Kat/images/Katpix.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   The Battle of Wills </span><hr size=1>  &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  The night was long and cold, sleep did not come to me.  My heart was aching for my losses, both Caddil and our child, gone from me.  I meditated  in prayer to Mother Tunare for the strength of spirit and soul I would need for the battle ahead with Farvak .  One that would not be  with weapons but of Wills. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I heard someone approach in the darkness that was just before the dawn.  I could see only shadows.  Suddenly cold water poring over my body. Surprised, but  quickly thinking I took this opportunity to wash some of the dirt off my face.  This action surprised whoever was there, a gasp of breath was the giveaway, they left as silently as they came. I did my best to put some order to my hair and straighten the torn dirty clothing.  I then again turned to prayer and meditation, awaiting the day's tortures.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp It wasn't long till Farvak entered,  &quot;Ah, I hear you enjoyed your shower this morning.  Well good, we will keep you happy then.&quot;  he said.  He then walked over to the a wolf that was tethered across the barn.  Farvak  took out his knife and cut off an ear leaving the wolf howling in pain. &quot; I think that you should have a wolf skin pelt to wear and this one will do nicely&quot; he said tossing the ear to me.   He waited watching for my reaction to this.  I humbly bowed to him keeping my eyes on his feet.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp He walked over to me, the tension between us made made the air thick.  He knelt down lifted my head wanting to peer into my eyes.  But I kept them from him, looking every where but in his eyes.   This only angered him and he slapped me hard across my cheek.  I again returned to the bowed position tasting the blood in my mouth from a split lip.    He stood up and kicked my side and then commanded &quot;Kiss my boots, Kat. Now&quot; I quickly obeyed him and lowered my lips to his boots, I felt the anger rise in my head. I reminded myself that this was exactly what he wanted from me my anger and pride. I took a deep breath and let the anger slip from my mind. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp He spat on me disgusted that he could not get the reaction he wanted.  He turned and grabbed the wolf and slit its throat and left.  The animal's eyes showed surprise as it gasped for its last breaths.  I said a prayer for my brother wolf and only then shed a tear for his suffering, as the blood oozed from the now limp body.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp A servant came in skinned and prepared the wolf for cooking.  I could smell the odors from the kitchen wafting through the air mixed with the smell of blood ,urine and stench of the barn.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Farvak returned an hour later, grabbed a shovel from the wall and ordered me to start cleaning up, &quot;I had to earn my keep here&quot;.  He sat down on a barrel and watched as I obeyed him.  He was eating an apple, slicing off pieces, putting the piece in his mouth and chewing all the while describing how good it was, how juicy.  Then he started speaking of me in the same manner. <br>
<br>
      &quot;You know Kat your like this apple.  If taken to soon from the tree you would be bitter and tough to eat.  But I will wait till it is time for you to be taken, you will be sweet, juicy and wonderful&quot;.  He then came up behind me and stood so that his body was against my back.  When I didn't react to him he put his hands around my body and pulled me to him.  Whispering with his rough beard against my cheek &quot;I will have your rage, I will have you.&quot; then he backed away and pushed me into the filth, laughing at me.  I landed on my knees and hands in  the muck that came up to my elbows and smelled like sewage.  I waited for his orders all the while trying to control my temper. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I slowly stood up and continued to shovel the mess from the barn.  It was then that  Farvak left, this battle would be long and hard. <br>
<br>
       A servant came in and watched as I finished the job that was apparently his.  The whole time he laughed while eating and drinking, He said through a cheery voice &quot;Boy, am I glad you came along,  my days have just gotten easier.  You will now do my tasks&quot;.  The job completed I was again chained to the wall, the servant left.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I again returned to my meditative prayer &quot;Oh, Mother Tunare I know what you want of me, please see me through this give me the strength to control my temper, pride and rage. Give me the spiritual fortitude to complete this task.  Let my soul find peace no mater what is done to my body&quot;.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Farvak entered smiling,  &quot;We have need of entertainment, Kat and it looks like your going to be it.  The children are bored and have asked for a game.  Since I killed their pet,  you get to take its place&quot;.   He took me out into the yard area and locked my chains to a post that had rings on it for just such a purpose.  Then walked to the chairs beside the house where more men sat.  The children, demon possessed came piling out of the house armed with wooden swords and weapons.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Farvak said &quot;Well look what we have here a wild beast, a filthy animal of Mother Tunare's.  Show me children what we do to anything so vile in our forest&quot;  Quickly they came charging at me holding weapons overhead shouting gleefully at the prospect of a real live elf to kill.  I prepared myself for the worst, it was then that I saw a scaly creature amongst the brush weapon drawn and ready.  He looked as though he would gladly take on the whole of the house. This must be the friend Kygero spoke of,  my guardian.  I shook my head  no, and only hoped he would not come to my aid.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Time and time again I would be bludgeoned and near death when a cleric would heal me and the game would start again. Only when the children became bored with this and there was a call to come eat was I returned to my place in the barn. The cleric's last heal were just enough so that I could  feel the bruises, pain  and broken skin..<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp   It was then that Kygero came to me giving me my requested spell book, food and water.  I drank and ate while she healed my wounds. She shook her head  at what she saw.  Sadness  filled her eyes as she looked at my body. I could feel her anger rise  and I knew that i needed to say something. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  I said &quot;Your friend has a tough job.  To stand by and watch this will be hard for both he and you.  Understand, please, you  must leave me to this, it is important that I consume Farvak's mind.&quot;  Her nod of understanding did not erase the sadness as she spoke.  She  told me of the blessings given and all of my family wished for my safety. That all those in the Bronze Dragon Fellowship worried but understood that my orders came from Tunare.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp   I said  softly &quot;Farvak will not allow me to die so do not worry there. He is obsessed with my rage and anger and as long as I can, with the help of Mother Tunare, keep that out of his reach he will make sure I live. Now time for you to go&quot;.   I could see in her face the outrage that she felt towards all who would hurt me. I knew she left me only because of our faith in Tunare. I hid the rations, the water and sat to memorize the spells I would need to keep myself alive.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  I heard footsteps and quickly hid my spell book.   A woman dressed in fine silks came out to me with water and food.  Speaking with disgust and anger she said &quot;You have his attention now, how I hate you!  My hate will keep him by me for a while.  He has sent me out here to tend to you so that my anger will delight him tonight.  But it is you he wants.  Although from what I've seen I can't imagine why. Your a weak and stupid girl for letting him catch you.  You have no fire that I can see, no your just another elf with the sickening light that will be crushed all to soon.&quot;  I didn't reply and she left.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  Alone in the barn, I tore a small piece of cloth from my clothing, what was left of it.  Rinsed it in the water and then washed myself as best I could.  I was so tired from the days events, emotionally and physically exhausted.  I soon drifted off to sleep.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I woke up to find Farvak kneeling by my side with a piece of straw tickling my arm lightly, then whispering in my ear..&quot;Dreaming of Caddil where you&quot;  He then straddled me and lowered himself down on my stomach.  I again would not look him in the eyes, I kept my head turned from him. Grinning he  ripped the last shred of clothing off of my body.  I made no movement to resist him or hide my nakedness. His hands touched my skin, his fingers cold and hard he moved them to my chin turning my head to his gaze.  I closed my eyes again avoiding eye contact.  He then moved his hands down my body .  I could feel his gaze hard, cold and hungry. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  Your to dirty for me to soil myself with now so we shall bath you.   He marched me out into the yard where the animal water trough was. He ordered me to step in and sit down, I did exactly as he said.  He took a rough brush and scrubbed me raw.  The water cold the air even  more so.  The dark elves from inside the house came out to watch as he pushed my head under the water, holding me there till I though my lungs would burst.  Then let me up and breath.  They all laughed  as I gasp for air.  Then he had me stand up naked in front of these people for their inspection.  &quot;She clean enough to come in the house now&quot; he asked them laughing. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  &quot;Yes come bring her in by the fire it is to cold for me to stand out here waiting for you. I will see what I can do to cloth her ugly white body, I won't look at it any longer&quot;  came the answer.  As I walked passed the group they each took a swat at my butt, feeling the sting I was lead to the fire.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Farvak said &quot;She needs to be clothed in your finest love.. I wish to take her to  the Temple of Innoruuk.  I wish her to see the power of my God.  To know and learn to fear me and respect all that Innoruuk  is&quot;.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;You cant take her there,  no one will let you in with her looking like this&quot; came the voice of a woman.   Farvak's voice now sharp  &quot; I know. so you must dress her so that she can be taken in.  Hide her, cover her well.  Do not disappoint me or you will be chained in the barn tonight and she will be in your bed.&quot;  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Damn you Farvak&quot; she said as she angrily waked out of the kitchen.  He then turned to me and chuckled, proud that he had got a rise out of her. His grin charming and yet menacing.  &quot;Well now lets see what can I do to help you let go of your anger&quot;  he walked over to me smiling evilly &quot;I have been to gentle with you, Kat.  I feel the need to see pain in your eyes&quot;.  He grabbed my arm and turned me so that I faced the group of men standing at the door.  &quot;You see them each of them would like to know what it is like to touch you.  Each would like to rip you apart.  Your life is mine, your body is mine and I will let them have you when I tire of you&quot;  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I closed my mind to this thought and again reminded myself that it wasn't my body, but my rage he wanted.  Let the anger go I prayed let me be strong enough not to let it control me.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp It was then that his wife returned with clothing. Seeing him touching me, holding me, her face twisted in anger.    She picked up a knife off of the table and started for Farvak swearing, shouting, at the top of her lungs.  &quot;I am going to kill you and that whore of an elf Now!!&quot;.  Farvak turned grabbed her arm and pushed her to the floor. Laughing at her he told the men at the door to take her and do as they will she needed to be taught who was the Master here.  &quot;Bastard&quot; she shouted &quot;You will pay dearly for this&quot;. As she was lead out of the house.   <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp He picked up the pile of clothing the ordered the servants to dress me.  He sat and watching them telling them this was good or that wouldn't do. When I was dressed to his saticfation.  He said to me &quot;She will be very ripe tonight.  Her anger will make her passionate and her body will bend to me and my will.  Soon yours will do the same. I love a woman with fire that is ablaze.&quot;  His eyes cold and hungry with the desire to hurt something.  I thought he would rape me there in front of the servants, on the table.  But instead he  walked out of the  room.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Through Neriak to the Temple of Innoruuk  I was lead.  It was in the Temple where I saw the true face of evil. The pleas for help unanswered, the evil delights of all wicked things could be found here. Chaos abounded here no order no reason just evil.  Farvak's eyes gleamed with pride at all of this.  His smile broad and he walk proudly strutting.  He was powerful here, there were those who bowed to him and gave him leeway.  Mostly the place reeked of fear.  Evil wears many faces and the ones I saw here were sickening.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Farvak seemed to absorb the energy from the very ground itself here.  How was I ever going to be strong enough to overcome this place, this man. Our visit was short, and on our way out of the Temple who was there but Iszabelle.  She stood and smiled at Farvak with the same hunger he had had in his eyes in the kitchen that morning.  &quot;Where have you been Farvak I have need of you&quot;.  He smiled and waved her to follow him.  I behind the both of them.   <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Farvak proud that he had been successful at sneaking me into the Temple of Innoruuk was now a bit nervous with Iszabelle here. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  Her voice tensed with anger &quot;Farvak what the hell is this.  Tell me now why have you not responded to my request for your presents.  I need you to help finished my plans for Gorsha.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp   &quot;Please Iszabelle I will tell you as soon as we are out of here Please follow me.&quot;  Iszabelle not use to being ordered stopped in her tracks &quot;Farvak tell me now, I am your mistress and you obey me remember&quot;.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  &quot;Quickly then come here into this doorway.&quot; He almost pleaded.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Yes fear was the stench that controlled everything here, even Farvak.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;That isn't my wife&quot; he spoke softly.  Then smiling he said &quot;I have Kat. I am going to break her, to make her mine&quot;.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp   Iszabelle looked perturbed now &quot;So you have Kat and you now can ignore me.  I think not&quot;  You are to be my servant remember all you have is because I allow you to have it&quot;. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  Anger now rose in Farvak's eyes. &quot; Do not speak to me so in front of her&quot;.  He grabbed my arm and pulled down the veils that covered my face. Iszabelle looked a bit shocked as she suddenly understood why he had not stopped and given her due respect. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  &quot;You fool&quot; she spat &quot;How can you bring her to our Temple.  How can you show such little respect for our GOD&quot;  She was even more angry at him. &quot; You think that by showing  her our GOD she will change&quot;.  <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I wanted to show her the true power our GOD has here that her beliefs where simply weak and stupid rules.  Traditions that controlled the people through superstition&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Let us get her out of here your mind is clouded and your not thinking clearly of your duties to me&quot;. She said disgusted.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp We were well out of Neriak when they spoke again. &quot;Farvak you have pushed to far this time I will take Katreena and give her to Trax. To do with as he will. You are losing control of yourself with this desire to have her&quot;  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp   He was now standing his shoulders set, his full height menacing towards her  &quot;I think not,  she is mine.  I have waited years for her and I will not give her to anyone.  Not even you Mistress. I will kill all who try to take her from me.  I admit I have been lax in my duties to you.  But do not think that you can take her without a fight&quot;  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Oh very well then, keep her but do not let her interfere with My orders to you again or I will see both of you dead&quot;. She said firmly  &quot;Your a fool you know, she will never change and you will kill her in the end.  Her strength comes from her beliefs in Tunare.  But if you can break that then you will have won a prize worthy of your talents indeed&quot;.  Farvak grinned and marched on ward to his home. <p>Katreena Wanderheart 40th Leaf Master Brewer <br>
