    <br>
    Farvak's mood was of a proud peacock, delighted with the charade at the Temple and then to be able to bring Iszabelle to his home.  He seemed unmoved by his wife's fuming nature nor by the disapproving looks Iszabelle was casting his way. <br>
<br>
    The best seats were made available food and drink were brought.  Farvak turned to his wife and said  &quot;Take Kat to my bedroom now&quot;.  Her look was one of ice and fire.  All he did was chuckle as he took a bite of  fruit.  <br>
<br>
    I was lead upstairs to a large room with a bed  at one side.  She quickly took the clothes from me.  Glaring she said&quot;I will have to burn these now there is no hope of ever getting your stench off them&quot;. <br>
<br>
    Left alone and naked, I pulled a blanket off the bed and wrapped it around me. I wanted nothing more than to be in the barn with my meditative prayer, my spell book and my solitude.  So now what, what did Farvak think he was up to tonight. I studied the room and all that was there.  The hour was getting late and there was nothing more to do so I sat down on the bed to meditate and pray for the strength that only Mother Tunare could give me.  <br>
<br>
    I heard voices outside the door. Farvak said  &quot;I have no more need of you Jess.  I told you to dress Kat this morning.  That if you didn't do this you would be sleeping in the barn and so you shall&quot;  She kept her voice low but the threat was still there &quot;If you do this to me tonight I will not be here tomorrow&quot;.   Farvak laughed &quot;So be it, You leave with only what you have on you now.  If you take anything from here you will be arrested for thievery and be punished so&quot;.   The voices trailed off and then Farvak entered the room. <br>
<br>
    &quot;I think I owe myself a treat tonight Kat, and your it&quot;  He came to my side and touched my cheek.  I didn't move or respond, although inside I felt myself tighten at his touch, revolted by it.  &quot;Humm, how will you please me tonight&quot;? He said with a whimsical tone.  Then his hand came full force across my face, stinging and shocked. I looked at him.  &quot;Yes that is better, I was beginning to wonder&quot; there was that smile that chilled me to the bone.  Quickly I lowered my eyes, knowing I had given myself away.  <br>
<br>
    Iszabelle has need of your druid talents tomorrow and you will obey her.  But tonight you are mine alone.  There was a knock at the door, a servant came in with a jug of wine and glasses then left without a sound.  Farvak got up from my side and walked over to the glasses and pouring wine into both he said you need to drink this it will help you through the night.  He chuckled as he poured a potion into one glass and handed it to me.  &quot;Drink&quot; he ordered. <br>
<br>
    My face still stinging I took the glass and did as he ordered.  The room became soft at the edges and I  felt the warmth of the liquid flowing through my body.  Try as I might my thoughts would not remain clear.  <br>
<br>
     Then I felt his hand on me, no longer able to control my temper in this state, I was fighting back.  My composure gone, I was speaking angrily to him, all of my hate pouring out for all he had done to me and I couldn't seem to stop.  He was holding me down with the weight of his body now on mine. He  was tense with excitement.  His voice trailing somewhere far off as his hands becoming more rough as they roamed my body.  Forcing me, hurting me.  A slap across my face and his laugh it all became so much like a dream, a nightmare. <br>
************************************************************<br>
         Jess Farvak's wife found herself out in the barn.  Outraged that she had been put out of her own bed. <br>
         &quot;Damn him Damn him and that pastey white wood elf May Innoruuk have you both&quot; she said with clenched teeth.  Looking around she found the cleanest place she could to lay down and sleep for the night.  &quot;We will see who has the last laugh my sweet Farvak&quot; plans forming in her mind.<br>
<br>
       She would have left him a year ago but he had come into power being one of the Plague Bringers.  This had raised her status as well.  He had been away so she had the run of the place and his name.  Now it had all gone sour with his return and bringing that creature with him. <br>
<br>
       It was in the morning after a restless sleep that daybreak had offered her enough light to see the corner of a carefully wrapped book hidden under the straw. &quot;Ah she is a spy and this is proof.  I will give this to Iszabelle and be done with both make him look like he is in on a conspiracy&quot; <br>
<br>
        It would have been so simple to do but Farvak had come in to greet her.  &quot;I trust you slept well Love&quot; he taunted.  She sat up startled by him. &quot;Oh your hiding something come now let me have it&quot;  Knowing him she dare not try to keep it from him.  &quot;Damn&quot; she though &quot;Damn, damn, damn&quot; she had missed her chance.<br>
<br>
         She handed him the book looking sheepishly up saying &quot;See that elf is a witch, a spy.  Look what was in the hay here&quot;  Farvak's smile turned into a wide grin  This was the one thing he had hoped for.  He could now get rid of this &quot;dead weight&quot; and have his Kat too.  Oh how delightful things had turned out for him.<br>
<br>
************************************************************<br>
    I awoke to  Farvak grinning at me as he held my spell book out to me.  <br>
&quot;So there is a bit of dishonesty in you, how delightful.  Kat you've been hiding things from me haven't you.  Just as well you have this book but only when I see fit to give it to you. Iszabelle was right you will be the one to bring about the downfall of the Bronze Dragon Fellowship&quot;  His laugh turned menacing now. &quot;Up Kat  here get dressed in these&quot;. He through some tattered leathers at me.<br>
<br>
    I dressed as quickly as I could under his gaze.  He smiled as he looked me over his eyes hungry with that need to cause pain look. He held my arm tightly as we approached Iszabelle who was sitting at the table eating.  He lead me to a chair in the corner and handed me a plate of what looked to be scraps.   He ordered &quot;Sit and Eat&quot;  then turned to Iszabelle smiling. &quot;See Mistress she is as tame as any pet I have ever had&quot;  <br>
<br>
    Iszabelle glanced over and said &quot; Yes well be careful of that one she will turn on you as quickly as you have seemed to tame her&quot;  Farvak snickered &quot;No tame isn't the word I would use more like under control.  I like my pets wild and able to bite back&quot;  He glanced my way it was then that I saw there were scratches on his cheek.  He touched them with his fingers then gave me a smile.<br>
<br>
    Iszabelle said &quot;Well can she, or more to the point will she, teleport us to Kunark and insure our safety to reach our brethren there in Cabilis&quot;  Farvak  said &quot;You doubt my  ability to control her&quot;raising an eyebrow.    &quot;Lets get started then shall we&quot; Iszabelle said<br>
<br>
    I somehow had to get this information to Rashek this could be the one weapon that I could use  to help The Bronze Dragon Fellowship to defeat the Plague Bringers.  I needed to gain what trust I could of Farvak and Iszabelle now.  To become their means of transportation could mean that I had the ability to know where their forces would gather. <p>One Very Adventurous Druid<BR>Katreena Wanderheart 41st Leaf Master Brewer <BR>
