ss=title>   Expressions</span><hr size=1> A young lad dressed in torn cloth was instructed to deliver a box to Rashek at Highhold Pass.  He traveled to the city on the mountaintop.  Buildings were carved into the mountains side, he was impressed to finally see a city he had heard about.  He asked one of the guards for the location of the inn. <br>
<br>
 The corridor was long and the winding stairs ended to the 2nd floor.  Around the corner he saw the room number and knocked.  A lovely lady had answered the door.  She was a radiant with auburn hair.  She was smiling holding onto the door.  How can I help you?    The boy began to stutter and looked away,  I have a package t t t to deliver for Rashek.   Ah, you have found the right place: however, he is not here. I will take the package and make sure that he will get it.<br>
The boy handed the box to Kuvanu.  As she laid her hands upon it, she felt a cold chill run through her body, she instantly wanted to drop the box but she had held on to it and placed in on the wooden table quickly.  She thanked to boy and closed the door. <br>
<br>
Kuvy wanted to know what was in the box.  Her curiosity was urging her to open it. I can take a peak at it, he will be home soon.  She slowly opened the box and noticed that the box was lined with a protective covering.  A cloud of mist was obscuring the view.  She slid her hands into the box and lifted the object out. Kuvys eyes froze.  The screams echoed through the inn.  She dropped the head of Warpoet onto the floor.  She tried to wipe the blood off her hands on her clothes and sat on the floor as tears were streaming down.  The door opened with such force that it cracked. Rashek had rushed in and saw his wife in a corner cover in blood. What happened! What happened! Dear! he cried out.  Who did this to you and where are you cut!  He turned to grab a towel to clean the blood and noticed that head of Warpoet on the ground with a note pinned to his forehead.  Rashek sat on the floor. Stunned. He couldnt say a word but to mourn. He took Kuvy around the shoulder and hugged her, letting her know that things will be better. <br>
<br>
Iszabelle sat down and smile. &quot;I wish I could have let him alive. I have Phyllis and Kelee now but that will change soon.  I will sacrifice Phyllis and make Kelee a slave forever.  She does have a beautiful voice.&quot;  I wish I could be there to watch the reaction of Rashek, as she began to laugh.<br>
