</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cac3ab><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ukyalynn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kya Lynn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#c54400>(11/12/00 2:41:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Searching for Kat</span><hr size=1> Mythias pondered on the events that he saw over the past couple days at his post watching Kygero's guild sister, Katreena. Not sure of wether to contact Kygero when he saw Iszabelle walking with Farvak and Katreena, he decided to hold off and see what happens. Nothing did and Iszabelle took her leave from them as Farvak, with Katreena in tow, made their way back to the little house. Shortly after their arrival, he watched as Fravak's wife went fuming into the barn and stayed there over night. It was obvious what Farvak had planned with Katreena for the evening and it made him sick to think of what that was. Maybe he should try and rescue her??? No, that was made clear when she bade him to stay back on his first attempt to intervene, as those evil children used her for sword practice. He would wait this one out too. The evening passed and at daybreak, Farvak came out of his house to enter into the barn. After a few minutes had passed, he walked out of the barn with Katreena's spellbook in hand!! That could not be good. And the look on Farvaks wife's face, she agreed. To make matters worse, Iszabelle arrived at the house with a small escort. They entered when Farvak answered and have yet to show themselves since. With that, he made his decision to contact Kygero.<br>
Mythias concentrated and focused on the one mind he looked for. &quot;Kygero my friend, we have trouble!&quot; He quickly explained all that happened. &quot;And that wasss about sssixxx hoursss ago when the entered the houssse!&quot;<br>
&quot;O.k. Mythias, good job. They must have used Katreena to port them all somewhere, damn, that could be any druid ring. Stay there in case they return and i will have to go druid ring hopping to see if anyone saw them. Get a hold of me immediately upon sight of them and i will gate back there to you.&quot;, i responded.<br>
&quot;I will fair one, be careful!&quot; and Mythias's watery sounding voice disipated from my mind as he went back to his vigilant watch.<br>
Now this could be a problem, trying to find them now with the help of Katreena porting them who knows where, it was gonna be tough! Oh well, only one thing to do and that was get started on the druid rings to see if anyone had seen them. I sat and began my memmorizing of the different druid ring spells. Hmmmm, where would they go that would benefit them... let's try the Karanas first seeing as how Iszabelle has plans for Gorsha and that's where he is. Casting the appropriate spell for the North Karana Druid ring, i was gone and traversing the darkness to my destination. I stepped out of the dark and found firm footing. Hastely i went to the Druids there and asked them each if they had seen the people i described. Neither had and i decided to ask everyone in earshot. Again no noe had seen them. So not here, lets try Feerrot as it is an evil place and they would be welcome. The gate was open before me and in seconds i was standing at the foul Feerrot ring. Shouting out to all the same questions of possible sightings i got no answer. I repeated the question a couple times and someone answered that no one had seen the Plague Bringers around. Thanking them i then called the spirits to take me to Lavastorm. Unfortunately, i met with the same answers there as in Feerrot. At least these three zones were clear and i sat to rememorize ring spells.<br>
Next to Steamfont where i found the same results and on to Butcher Block. The druid there told me that no Plague Bringers had come through this ring. Alright, on to West Commons. There were alot of people at the ring today. Unfortunately, there were alot of evil people here today as well hunting the druids here at the ring. It always saddened me to see how the evil creatures camp our beloved ring and attack all the druids that Tunare blesses the ring with. But alas, it will always be that way and as i found on my first visit to this ring, there is nothing to be done, except pray to Mother Tunare for there souls. As i mentioned Katreena's name to the druids there, two of them said that they had seen her by herself in torn rags. She gated in and moved off quickly instead of greeting them as she usually did. They figured something wrong but could do nothing as their hands were full with the evil bastards that hunted them. I told them that i understood and then bade them thanks and good fortune. I looked over to where the evil ones camped. Well.... maybe they had seen something. Walking over to where they were sitting, they all turned and gave me an icy glare. With my head held high, i dared to ask, &quot;Has anyone seen any of the Plague Bringers come through here as of late?&quot;<br>
There was laughter and snickers from all. &quot;Like we would tell you if we had stupid druid, you are lucky we do not get up and throttle you!&quot; one of them by the name of Everkill answered. Again the laughs.<br>
&quot;Inc!!&quot; i heard one of their pullers say and the evil little beasts all rose as one and commenced to destroying another of Tunare's children.<br>
&quot;Does this look fun to you druid? Would you like to take the place of this poor fool? Then we can kill you instead!!!&quot; another of the wretched dark ones said. And then the laughs went into an uproar and the druid was dead.<br>
I winced as this did hurt me to watch, but keeping my cool i spoke again, &quot;I offer 10pp to any that knows anything about what i ask!&quot;<br>
At the mention of platinum, all got silent and looked and me curiously. Everkill was the one who spoke up, &quot;Make it 20pp and i will tell you what you want to know!&quot;<br>
&quot;Very well, but your information had better be good! Now first tell me what i want and then i will give you the money.&quot;, i answered.<br>
The others here all gave Everkill a look of confusion at which he said, &quot;Platinum is platinum and the Plague Bringers never gave me any.&quot; He turned to me and began, &quot;I saw the one called Farvak invisible from nomal sight and he was holding on to a druid like yourself but dressed in leather rags. It seemed he was controling her and forcing her to move east with him. She was not looking good at all, so i'd say this Farvak has done a great job!! If only we could all have a druid to control, Norrath would be a better place. HAHAHAHAHAHAHA!!!&quot; And of course all present began to roll around laughing. These horrid creatures had no right to live, i hope a griffon comes along here soon!<br>
&quot;Now my 20pp light skin!!&quot; Everkill shouted over the tumult of laughter and pointing.<br>
&quot;Yes, your 20pp... as i promised, so it shall be. I will leave you with the knowledge that unfortunately your god can never overcome the light and so shall stay in the darkness forever, may your false god live as he lives, in chaos and decide to kill you all for the fun of it as you do the druids here!!&quot;, i finished and began walking back to the druid ring.<br>
&quot;Thanks for the 20pp's stupid druid!! May Tunare contract the plague herself and die!!! HAHAHAHAHAHAHA!!&quot; as one started to laugh they all had to join in again.<br>
I turned and winked at him as i stopped and began calling upon all the spirits i know one by one and buffed the druids at the ring. There was an uproar of anger and filthy curses hurled at me from the evil encampment. I merely laughed back at them and said, &quot;Good hunting, foul smelling beasts!! HAHAHA&quot;<br>
The curses continued and i couldn't help myself, &quot;Hail a Griffon.&quot; i said.<br>
Everyone of them jumped up and began searching the skies. A few of them even ran without waiting for the others to confirm. I got the last laugh there, but it was time to move on. The spirits gathered about me and i was camoflaged and heading east.<br>
Reaching out i contacted Mythias, &quot;Mythias, i believe that Katreena and Farvak are on their way back, keep an eye out and i'm on my way now. I would gate there, but i wanna run it in case they stop and i can catch up to them. If they show before i get there then i will gate, so keep me informed!!&quot;<br>
Mythias responded, &quot;Yesss Kygero, i will. And thisss time, they will not lossse usss!!&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ada07e><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ukatreena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katreena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight, Order of Talon</span><br>  Posts: 281<br> <font color=#c54400>(11/15/00 2:14:36 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/soyouthinkiam/eq/Kat/images/Katpix.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   New's both good and Bad for Iszabelle</span><hr size=1> The night had been as I had feared, Farvak using and abusing my mind and body Not trying to break my spirit but to turn my soul  into something vile and evil to serve him only.  He spent hours delighted by my rage as I battled within myself.  He knew to well just how to get the reactions he wanted.  First he would torture me then allow me to let my rage out on him then show kindness that was so tender, only to return to the torture again.  It was a cycle of anger, action, and then guilt.    He would let me heal myself but not him.  I had left him with some very nasty wounds that would take days to heal and he seemed proud of them.  The pain from each one delighted him as if each one was an award for my soul sinking into his hell.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I awoke to knocks at the door and a voice calling in &quot;Time to get moving we have a lot to accomplish today&quot;.  Stirring, I felt arms around me,  I remained, comforted only for a second, before I remembered who's arms they belonged to.  Tremors of shame and rage ran through my body and mind.  I quickly stood up gathered my clothing, putting it on I turned to see Farvak smiling at me.  He said &quot;Oh you are so sweet when you dream an angel and yet I know just how evil you can be&quot;  his fingers finding a scratch touching it longingly.  &quot;Love wounds, you are delightful my pet&quot;  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Those words hurt me to the bottom of my heart &quot;My pet&quot;, Caddil was the only man who had used that term and when he had said it it was as if Mother Tunare had whispered it.  Now when Farvak said it it was like hell reaching up and pulling me down drowning me slowly. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I knew Farvak saw my pain as he pulled the covers back and step out of bed towards me.  He grabbed my waist and pulled me close his beard scratching my face he kissed me hard.  &quot;Good morning, to you&quot;. He said grinning.  My hand raised up to slap him when I caught myself. &quot;Oh go ahead dear one show me you love me. It will make my morning perfect&quot;  Ashamed, I lowered my eyes.  He pulled my chin up and looked at me &quot;Yes we still have work to do, but the task is one I am enjoying very much&quot; he then slapped my butt &quot;Here pick up my clothes and dress me, Kat&quot;.  I did as he bid me my face still flushed with temper.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp We met Iszabelle down in the dinning area she seemed in very good spirits as a young boy stood at her side, she handed him a bag full of money smiling like the cat who ate the best rat.   &quot;Hello Farvak&quot; she said  &quot;You must have had a very good night by the looks of you this morning&quot; giggling.  &quot;Here have some warm mead and food.  Then you must go to West Commons then on to the underworld of Freeport I have a list of things that you must get and people you must teleport here.   If we are to be successful with our next move against the Bronze Dragon scum we will need to move quickly.  Oh and I want to go to Feerrott I will be taking some help with me.  It is time for me to get Gorsha&quot; her laugh was so vile that it sent chills up my spine.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;You will then meet me and teleport me back here&quot; she handed a list to Farvak.  He looked a bit perturbed at being ordered around like a pack mule but took the parchment putting it in his pouch as he sat down to eat. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp   I stood behind him waiting,&quot;Sit down on the floor Kat, at my feet&quot;. I obeyed without hesitation.  All the others in the room even the servants stopped to stare as Farvak would place food in my mouth.  &quot;He said proudly &quot;yes she is the finest pet, I believe, I have ever had. Delightful at night and well behaved during the day&quot;  He grabbed my hair and held my head as he leaned over and kissed me hard.  &quot;Here  is some water my Lovely little Kat&quot;.  Grinning he handed me a glass of water.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Iszabelle looked my way disgusted and said &quot;Farvak you are to distracted by her but as long as she does my bidding during the day You may do as you will with her at night&quot;  They looked at each other and chuckled as if they both shared the same thought about me.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  &quot;You should have seen her.  She is appropriately named. She was a wild cat last night and a snuggling cat this morning&quot; Farvak said touching a wound left by me.  I winced at the words and his thought.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Breakfast done those that were going with us to Antonica gathered I was given my spell book.  Memorizing the Druid Rings for everyone's destination and then using the camouflage spell to cover our arrival we were off.  Iszabelle to Feerrott with her party, Others to North Karanas, and then Farvak and I to West Commons. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  When we arrived there were a group of dark elves were killing the Druids at the ring.  How cruel to see this and yet they were given the freedom of death I wished I had been so lucky.  Farvak smiled their way and  joined in the laughter as one of the Druids fell in death.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp We moved quickly away and on to Freeport and to the sewers there.    Farvak had just about completed the list of task on the parchment when he said &quot;Time to go pick up Iszabelle, quickly at Feerrott Kat&quot;.  When we arrived I felt a chill from the mood of the group.  Iszabelle was now fuming She was shouting out orders to all.  Asking who was responsible for the escape and heads where going to roll.  At first I thought that Grosha had done something that had Iszabelle so mad.  But then I heard someone mention to Farvak &quot;Kelee and Phyllis have escaped, whoever was in charge of their keep is dead meat now&quot;.  Farvak smiled to himself as he knew that Iszabelle would be handling that matter personally and he would be left in charge. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Teleport me to LavaStorm, Now&quot; She barked.  Farvak handed me the spell book.     When we arrived she said &quot;Farvak you will be in charge till I return to the Docks Do not fail me, I want Gorsha there when I get back.&quot;  &quot;Yes, Mistress it will be done&quot; he reassured her.  I cast Spirit of Wolf on her and her party, they turned and with speed set off for Neriak.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Well, well my Kat lets see what kind of trouble we can get into&quot; he said smiling  &quot;I think we need to find Gorsha and I know just the way.  You can call to him, have him come to you, to your aid.  Yes that will work&quot;  I looked at Farvak in horror &quot;No&quot; slipped from my lips and just as fast  his hand was across my face.  &quot;You will do it or I shall find and kill other's of the Bronze Dragon till you do&quot;  Knowing Farvak this was not a threat but a promise.  So we teleported to North Karanas and headed toward the great stone bridge as I sat my mind to calling out to Gorsha.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Betrayal was all I felt.  Gorsha was a good friend.  Kygero my close sister had loved him she had confided in me only one time.   Now I was going betray both.  Damn how could I change this.  I saw no way out,  if I refused he would kill others and make me watch.  What could I do?<br>
