    I walked back over to where Iszabelle was standing watching my every move.  Her eyes dark, empty holes of blackness.  Her face as cold and calm as a dead sea, lovely to look at but holding so much danger under the surface.  The air was thick with tension between us as I approached her, our eyes locked as the challenge had begun.<br>
