    She was smiling now as if she finally understood all to well that I too had some knowledge of my fate to come. <br>
<br>
      I smiled back my voice more firm &quot;Your God has saw fit to kill my family. Without that 1st strike I would not have become so strong in my faith.  My own God filing me with the Light of the Righteous and Just.  Yours testing the strength and will by continuing to punish me without just cause.  Taking from me the only man I could love, stealing from my womb the child that was created from that love. Taking the only soft spots from my life that gave me reason to care for others.   I have learned my lessons well, don't you think?  I am like a sword of the best metals that have been fired and bound, enchanted made pure with lessons from both your God and Mine.  I hunger for your vile and evil blood,that of your Master and followers there will be no survivors or prisoners.   I am cold, hard and ready for what is next&quot;<br>
<br>
      &quot;You should know that I am the wild card that will destroy your kind.  Know  now that I have nothing more to lose.  If I die now, that in my death I play the martyr! not only to the Bronze Dragons but to Farvak and his &quot;loyal&quot; followers in the Plague Bringers, as well!  I have a win win situation destroying you from both inside and out.&quot;  I laid  down on the bed with an air of command knowing that I had the upper hand now.<br>
