    An electricity ran through the air as a rift opened and we were both teleported through time and space to the Druid Ring in North Karanas.  Iszabelle was taken aback at this, when we arrived she was quickly attacked by the druids that held vigilance there.  She had to quickly stepped into the shadows, retreat was all she could do to escape her death. <br>
<br>
       It was then that  I quickly gated back to the docks and the building where I was bound by more than my chains.  I cast Superior camouflage on myself and searched the building for Gorsha.  I found him and quickly gated out to the Druid Ring in East Karanas.  Then told him to head quickly to High Hold Keep, to contact Kygero, I would be in touch.  <br>
<br>
       I was headed to find Farvak, grinning as I now had again bested Iszabelle.  She had given me a tool, the plague to use against her own kind.  I was not done with the Plague Bringers or my plans to destroy them all. My reasons were personal, but my actions and deeds were by the will of Mother Tunare, herself.<br>
