Bekkaha moonhowler <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cac3ab><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ukyalynn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kya Lynn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#c54400>(11/29/00 2:39:56 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Taking Action</span><hr size=1> &quot;Listen to me Kygero, we can take Ragingwolf out and then we<br>
can concentrate on more important matters at hand! This foul<br>
creature has taken too many lives and too much of our time. He is nothing, and should be dealt with hastely!&quot;, my sister's logic was finally getting to me. Kaitlyne had a point, and i was tired of wasting hers and Mythias's time. All this waiting around for the Plague Bringers to make a move was wearing on everyone's nerves and patience. I had made up my mind.<br>
&quot;O.k. sis, you are right. Ragingwolf will be our first objective, then we will move on to the rest of the wretched Plague Bringers. I am going to retrieve Mythias from his post and we will join you. Do not make a move on him till we get there!! Just wait, it won't be long.&quot;, i replied.<br>
I could hear my sister's mental sigh of relief, &quot;You got it Kyg, i will be waiting... but hurry, he is in East commons now and i think he is headed to the Oasis to take the boat to Kunark. We have to stop him before he gets on the barge or we will lose him!&quot;<br>
Damn, Mythias and i will have to move fast to catch up to him. &quot;Enough talk then, on my way. Be careful sis, and don't let him on the barge!&quot;<br>
Kaitlyne responded, &quot;I will do my best, just hurry!&quot; and i felt her break the connection of our minds.<br>
Without preparing my self, i called the spirits to take me to my bind point. I stepped out of the darkness and right behind Mythias. Without turning around, Mythias spoke, &quot;Greetingsss Lady Kygero, your ssscent isss unmissstakable and i am glad you here. It ssseemsss that Katreena and the Plague Bringersss are not coming back here<br>
or at leassst not for a while.&quot; Finally turning to face me, i could see that there was a few long scratches, caked with dried blood running down his check. Yet he was smiling that sharp, toothy smile as if nothing was amiss.<br>
&quot;What happened to your face, Scaly one?&quot;<br>
His long, narrow tongue flicked out of his pointy toothed mouth to lick the wound, then he chuckled. &quot;I took the initiative and ssspoke with Farvak'sss wife while i waited.<br>
Ssshe wasss not very welcoming to me and ssshowed me that fire that Farvak must love in hisss women. Neverthelessss, ssshe did cooperate when i told her that Farvak had hisss coming to him and ssshe could help with it. That wasss all it took for her to loosssen her tongue. Guesssss what i found out? The Plague Bringersss have there head quartersss in the Overthere port cccity. Alssso, thier plansss are coming to a head.&quot;<br>
Well that explains Ragingwolf's reason for going to the Oasis and the docks there.<br>
Quickly, i sat and began memming the spells i would need for our trip and possible confrontation with Ragingwolf. When i was finished i stood and told Mythias what the plan was. He seemed to like the idea and was getting bored with his vigilant watch. He too then sat, pulled his book out and began to prepare.<br>
&quot;I am ready Kygero, let usss be off.&quot;<br>
Calling the spirits again to do my bidding, both our feet left the ground and the Scale of Wolf entered our body and we were off.<br>
We both ran in silence and stopped for nothing. Reaching the East Commons tunnel, i concentrated my mind and contacted Kaitlyne. &quot;Sis, where are you now?&quot;<br>
&quot;I'm running behind Ragingwolf, we just left the tunnel and am headed out into the desert. Where are you?&quot;<br>
&quot;Mythias and i are in the tunnel now and Tunare willing we will be with you soon! Hang in there Kait.&quot;<br>
&quot;No problem Kygero.&quot;<br>
Ahh, Northern Ro and the heat blasted desert surface. We left the tunnel and continued on. As we passed the undead ruined ring and derv camp, i picked up on my sisters tracks.<br>
Excellent, we were catching up, and just might be able to stop Ragingwolf before he gets on the barge to Kunark. The snake spire was just in sight when Kaitlynes tracks disappeared. That could mean only one thing, she and Ragingwolf had entered the Oasis. Pushing on, Mythias and i soon found ourselves in the Oasis as well and just in time. My sister called out to me, &quot;Sis, he is at the docks and the barge is here!!! Should i confront him and try to stop him from getting on the barge?&quot;<br>
As i was about to answer her, she started again, &quot;Wait, he just got off the barge and is now sitting on the dock, what is this all about?&quot;<br>
&quot;I don't know Kaitlyne, but good.&quot;<br>
Then i heard Mythias begin to chuckle.<br>
&quot;What is it snake breath?&quot;, i asked.<br>
&quot;We can ssstop Kygero, he isssn't going anywhere. I contacted him, insssult him, and challenged him to a duel. Hisss vanity got the bessst of him thisss time. He accccepted, we've got him now.&quot;<br>
&quot;That was good thinking Mythias, but he is a little more experienced than you.&quot;<br>
&quot;Yesss but, he doesssn't know about you and your sssissster.<br>
Buff me up and then ssstay out of sssite, just watch from a dissstanccce and heal me when i need it. By the time he figuresss it out, it will be to late for him.&quot;<br>
I began to laugh. This reptile was smarter than the average Iksar. &quot;What would i do without you Mythias?&quot; We both shared in a laugh then.<br>
&quot;Here is the plan Kaitlyne, Mythias challenged him to a duel. That is why he got off the barge. I will buff him and when they begin you watch him from the south side of the dock and i will watch from the north. When Mythias is almost downed, we begin to heal him. Ragingwolf will be helpless then to Mythias and we can take the bastard.&quot;<br>
&quot;Sounds like a plan Kyg. Lets do it!&quot;<br>
Again burrying my nose in my favorite book, i memorized all the good buff spells for Mythias. As i started to buff him, he too buffed himself and sat to meditate.<br>
&quot;With all thessse buffsss, i feel like i could take him and the whole of the Plague Bringersss on!&quot; Mythias was excited and his adrenaline was pumping for the battle ahead.<br>
&quot;Good, and remember, we have your back. Shall we?&quot;<br>
&quot;Oh yesss!&quot;, was his reply.<br>
With that we were off. I stayed behind the dune just north of the dock and called the Spirit of the Wolf and Superior Camoflauge on myself. Mythias went down to the dock and confronted Ragingwolf. I heard him challenge Ragingwolf to a duel and of course it was accepted. Everyone near the dock stopped what they were doing to watch and made room for the insueing battle.<br>
Ragingwolf let out a cry, &quot;You will die now by my hands you stupid reptilian beast!!&quot;<br>
Not saying a word, Mythias began casting. The battle was on.<br>
Getting the first blow in, Mythias diseased Ragingwolf and then pulled his Wraithbone Hammer out to go into melee. Fuming that he wasted his initiative, Ragingwolf pulled his own weapon and began to fight back. The battle went on for quite a while. The air was filled with magic and their weapons were drenched in blood. It looked as if Mythias might actually not need our help when Ragingwolf riposted a critical blow from Mythias. Ragingwolf came around and slammed his weapon into Mythias's head, knocking him back and nearly killing him. As if on que, Kaitlyne and i stood and called the spirits to heal our scaly friend. With both our heals soaking into Mythias, his wounds all closed and he<br>
started in again with refreshed eneregy.<br>
Outraged, Ragingwolf looked around and yelled out, &quot;What in the name of Innoruuk!! How dare someone help this beast while in a duel with me!!&quot; He looked up and saw me. His eyes bulged out and i could see why he got his name. It was appropriate for him. Everyone else that was sitting and watching also started to yell out that it was a forfiet duel.<br>
Stupidly, Ragingwolf did not turn to face Mythias in time to stop him from his downward thrust with the handle of the hammer on Ragingwolf's head. Ragingwolf's head split wide and the blood spewed out in all directions. He fell to the desert floor unconcience. Mythias hastely disarmed and tied up Ragingwolf. Kaitlyne and i came down the dunes and stood next to Mythias. All that was watching started in on us. Saying that we cheated and should let Ragingwolf go. I quickly explained all that was going on with the Plague Bringers and our Bronze Dragon Fellowship. I told them of the capture and destruction of some of our guild by theirs and that we were merely getting back at them. Most of the spectators were still confused but seemed to decide it wasn't there problem. Of course there was a few that continued putting up an argument but were quited by the others. Deciding it was time to make our departure, we gated out to the East commons with our quary.<br>
Carrying the prisoner, we took him to Highhold Keep where the other Bronze Dragons awaited. Camoflauging Mythias, we got him into our rooms and we all knelt in front of Lord Rashek.<br>
&quot;You and your small band have done well Kygero. My thanks to you Kaitlyne of the Order of Concord and Mythias of the Bloodtalon. Banlaen, Sloar, show our unwilling guest to the dungeon and put a watch on him.&quot; Rashek pointed to Ragingwolf and waved his hand in dismissall. The two Bronze Dragons grabbed Ragingwolf roughly and lead him away.<br>
Rashek continued, &quot;We will deal with him later and ask the questions that need to be answered. As for you three, get some food and rest. Plans are being made as we speak to deal with the Plague Bringers.&quot;<br>
&quot;Thank you M'lord, but i must tell you that Mythias has found out the where abouts of Iszabelle's head quarters. The port city of Overthere is where they are amassed.&quot;, i said.<br>
Rashek only smiled, &quot;Yes i know Kygero, someone has told me this already. He was captured by Farvak and then saved by our own Katreena and gated out. Gorsha is waiting for you in your chamber. Go to him.&quot;<br>
My face flushed with color and i moved to depart to my room when Rashek gently grabbed my arm.<br>
&quot;When you see him, do not be alarmed... but he has left our guild to join another. He is a brother to the Pax Maelstrom now. He still loves us and we him, but people change and he has decided to move to another family. It is his life to do with, and we will not shun him for his free will.&quot; and Rashek let go of me.<br>
Confused and some what disappointed, i went to my room while Kaitlyne and Mythias were made comfortable. What was this all about? I had just seen Gorsha not too long ago and he said nothing of his thoughts of changing guilds to me. My mind was racing now. Was it because i didn't marry him? He knows that my heart is his. Did he have problems with our guild or someone in it? Did the Pax Maelstrom plan to recruit him for a long time now? Or was it just a spontaneous decision? Like we needed more distractions from our present dangers. I stood in front of the door to my chamber thinking for what seemed an eternity, going over all and trying to figure out what to say. Suddenly the door swung open and there stood Gorsha. Looking at his dark skin and curly hair, memories and feelings came flooding back in a rush and all my doubts and questions were forgotten. I was just so glad to see him safe. I threw my arms around him, pushing him back into the room and quietely shut the door behind me. I would eat and rest later. All the while, in the back of my mind, i kept visualizing my guild sister Katreena's face. Mother Tunare please keep her safe and may she contact me soon! We need to know how she is and what she wants us to do! Watch over her Mother Tunare! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ada07e><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ukatreena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katreena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight, Order of Talon</span><br>  Posts: 312<br> <font color=#c54400>(11/29/00 1:41:37 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/soyouthinkiam/eq/Kat/images/Katpix.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   The Beginning of the End</span><hr size=1> &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I now called upon the Druids at the ring in West Commons opening the rift again and gating there.  I walked shyly over to the group of evil elves who found sport in killing the Druids at this ring.  I caught the eye of one of them and he started taunting me with names and spells.  I raised my eyes to meet his and asked &quot;Have you seen Farvak, my Lord and Master&quot;.  This stopped him and he looked at me in shock &quot;Farvak your Master, Druid?&quot; <br>
<br>
 &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  I lowered my eyes and said &quot;I am sorry for being so bold, but I must find him. I have my duties to him now.&quot;  He doubted my sincerity with more questions &quot;You wear the Bronze Dragon Fellowship Insignia, Druid! Why call Farvak your Master? He is of the Plague Bringers&quot;.  I knelt now and held my head low &quot;Please Sir, I am the plan that will bring down the Bronze Dragons.  I must find Farvak quickly.Lead me, if you will, to his side I know he will reward you well for this service&quot;.  I held my hands out and offered him my chains.<br>
<br>
  &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I could sense the change in him with the mention of reward as he took my chains.  He leaned over to the group he was with and laughed &quot;Look I have my own pet Druid to play with&quot;.  They laughed as he stood up and began to lead me on to Neriak and hopefully to Farvak.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp On through the woods then into the city following my captor who was enjoying the power of bringing in one such as I.  Vile insults were thrown at me as well as stones and spoiled foods.  He stopped at a bar and found out where Farvak was. <br>
<br>
A guard stopped us as we approached a building that had apparently seen some destruction my captor spoke with him and the guard turned entered the building. A few minuets later Farvak stood in front of me and my captor.  His eyes filled with suspicion as he saw me in tow.<br>
<br>
  &quot;Humm, now what have we here&quot;  He spoke with my captor and asked how he had come into possession of me and I knew that lies would be told here.  Farvak smiled and paid the man well with bags filled with gold.   He then garbed my chains and pulled me along into the building. <br>
<br>
 &quot;Well now it seems you have tried to escape again! My what fun we will have  getting to the truth of how you came to be here&quot; he said as we marched along.  &quot; Ah, maybe I can use your talents now to sort out this mess&quot;.  We stepped over bodies that  lay ripped, bloody and scattered on the floor.  &quot;Iszabelle should have been a bit more subtle than this if she is to have the support she needs to defeat the Bronze Dragons.  Killing her own  even if they were fools is not a good sign.  There are better ways to handle things and keep those you need close&quot;.   We stopped in front of a badly wounded dark elf who looked scared and quite shaken.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp   &quot;You can start with him&quot; Farvak waved his arm as he sat down in a large chair.  I healed the elf and then sat at Farvak's feet.  Farvak started questioning the elf and for every foolish answer the poor thing gave Farvak would strike him down.  Soon the story of what had happened according to this poor mans knowledge came out.  I again healed him and he was taken out to a room to eat and rest.  Farvak turned to me and said &quot;Well now, not much else we can do here I will leave it to the fools to clean up&quot;.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Time for you and I to return to Kunark, aye Kat&quot;   He said looking tired by the days events.  It was then that I spoke up &quot;Sorry to speak to you Lord&quot; I braced for the slap that should have come for speaking to him without permission.  &quot;I am afraid that Iszabelle is not going to be pleased.  She has granted me my freedom. This just after she had you leave.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp   Farvak's eyes filled with surprise and then rage.  &quot;What&quot; his voice roared.  Glaring at me with suspicion he then pulled at my chains so that I was close to him.  I dared not look at him, but could feel his hands grab my arms tightly, pulling me still closer. His breath  hot on my head his body so close to mine that I was bushing up against his strong muscular chest, feeling the warmth through his clothing. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I think you lie Kat.  Why are you here then&quot; his voice commanding an answer. So I gave him the truth, well sort of,  &quot; It was in my efforts to set Gorsha free that I was captured at West Commons Druid Ring.  I didn't get to bring my spell book when I left the docks I wasn't prepared to do battle then&quot;.  <br>
<br>
 &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Farvak laughed amused &quot;So she has lost three of her most valued prizes today.   She is a foolish woman.  Failure is all around her now!  It is time to report things to Iszabelle's Master, O'berton and perhaps get a promotion&quot;   His voice now filling confidence said  &quot;So now on to High Pass!&quot; he had let the words slip, then caught himself.<br>
<br>
 &quot;But we must be very careful as that is the stronghold of your guild.&quot;  He pulling my face so that our eyes met then said &quot;Wouldn't want you to trick me now would I &quot; there was a pause for a moment as he thought and then said &quot;So maybe, we will go to the docks of Kunark and see if your telling the truth first. We will pick up your spell book as well&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I thought to myself O'Berton was behind all this I how had a name and a location. High Hold Pass, this was all to convenient.  So this is how the Plague Bringers knew of the Bronze Dragons movements?  Yes, this was going to be tricky to get this information to Lord Rashek.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I was brought out of my thought by Farvak saying &quot;Are we ready to go, Kat?&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I quickly started casting the spell for the Gate to the Dreadlands Druid Ring the rift opened and we were again standing there in a most beautiful, but deadly valley.  The trees painted with leaves of gold, red and orange that danced in the wind. We ran to the tunnel that would lead us to a land frigid and iced over.  Then on to the Overthere where the fern and fauna were alive and deadly as well. <br>
<br>
When we reached the docks  Farvak was holding my chains he walked ahead of me through the streets to the building that was now the Plague Bringers Headquarters. The guards at the dock were all to familar with this scene to stop and question us. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp We entered the main floor as Iszabelle came down to meet us.  &quot;Farvak&quot; she said seductively &quot;I see Kat has brought you back.&quot;  His eyebrow raised &quot;Kat? brought me!&quot; he laughed.  Then said &quot;No, she was captured at the West Commons Druid Ring by one of our own there.  You were a fool to try and set her free Iszabelle!  You know that I am the one who controls her&quot; <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  Iszabelle's eyes flamed as she spat &quot;You are her puppet, fool, delusional!  Take her up to your room now!.  Then come back we have much to discuss.&quot;  Iszabelle's eyes said it all as she stared at me and said &quot;You will be dead by morning,Kat&quot;   I knelt down to both and then was lead off by Farvak to his room.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  Again chained to the wall I looked around knowing that this was right where I should be.  It was now that I said a prayer to Mother Tunare &quot;Thank you Oh wise and all knowing Mother of the Earth the Stars the Very essence of Norrath.  You have blessed me by delivering to me my enemies at just the right moment.  Lead me on let the knowledge and the power you have given me smite them down and destroy all of their kind.  Wipe the face of Norrath clean of their vile souls.  For Caddil, for my child for your Glory I pray.&quot;  <br>
<br>
  &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Knowing what she would tell Farvak about the details of our encounter earlier.  Yet knowing he would look and judge her by her actions, they had no trust in one another  words.  She would now be seen as woman who was trying to save face, all of the mistakes that had been made, all of her orders she had given that had lead to the escape of Phillys, Kelee and Gorsha. Clearly she was not the leader that  they thought she was.  The Plague Bringers would soon turn on her.  That was what I had as a weapon now, the plague that I would bring would be one of division and doubt.<br>
<br>
 <p>One Very Adventurous Druid<BR>Katreena Wanderheart 42nd Leaf Master Brewer <BR>
