herf=http://members.home.net/soyouthinkiam/eq/Kat/images/"target="web"><img src="http://members.home.net/soyouthinkiam/eq/Kat/images/Katreena.jpg" border="0"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cac3ab><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uiszabelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iszabelle</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.mmpog.net/EverQuest/BronzeDragon/Images/fadeskull.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#c54400>(12/2/00 12:42:57 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.mmpog.net/EverQuest/BronzeDragon/Imagesolf/Skull-33.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Regression</span><hr size=1> Iszabelle returned home from a long travel. The couple of days refreshed her mind and perspectives.  She knew she had to be prepared for anything.  Even though, Fravak may turn against her.  The plans were made and set to go if things didn't go well.<br>
<br>
She asked the guards to find Dekaarn and Ragingwolf.  She missed the barbarian and his companionship.  She knew he was always busy with the Iksar slaves and the mines in Frontier Mountains.  Iszabelle took a deep breathe and sighed.<br>
<br>
She paced the floors in her room.  She knew that Katreena asked to be brought to Fravak from the druid rings and she knew that she was free to go on her will.  This confirmed Iszabelle's suspicions.  She will use Fravak to destroy her.  She grabbed her cloak and disappeared into the darkness.<br>
<br>
Iszabelle enter the room as Fravak was pulling his pants up.  He blushed as he walked over to the chair to grab his tunic.  Katreena was asleep in the bed.  Iszabelle tried to contain her anger.  She looked hard at Fravak and told him to meet her downstairs.<br>
<br>
"I set her free, Fravak.  She's using you and yet you are blind," as she sat down staring at him.  "How dare you! Iszabelle. You think you know everything.  I love her and she will not do such a thing," as he paced the floors hard and avoiding eye contact with Iszabelle. <br>
"Fravak, you must kill her today.  If you don't, you will have to answer to me!"  She was eager to here his reply.<br>
"I will do no such thing!" as he shouted.  "If you touch her, I swear..." He words can to a sudden stop. He turned around to find Iszabelle missing. She had disappeared. Fravak let a sigh of relief. "I must hide her tonight and fake a death to make her trust me."  <br>
<br>
Upstairs, Katreena could here the augments.  She was please to see that her prayers were working to her advantage.  She knew that her returning would put a wedge between Iszabelle and Fravak. She dressed quitely feeling an odd sense that someone was watching her then she heard 'I'm watching you'.<br>
                    *****************<br>
<br>
Iszabelle gated to the Dreadlands. She stepped into the shadows and passed travelers to the city.  She followed the creek into the vast mountains.  The breeze carried a faint smell of death.  She took a deep breathe.  Iszabelle felt she was not in control. "Has the gods punished me! Have I done any wrong" as she shouted as the echoes traveled throughout the mountains.<br>
 <p><img
src=http://www.mmpog.net/EverQuest/BronzeDragon/Imagesolf/fadeskull.gif>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ada07e><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ukatreena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katreena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>BDF Officer</span><br>  Posts: 366<br> <font color=#c54400>(12/10/00 9:18:09 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/soyouthinkiam/eq/Kat/images/Katpix.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   The Last Stand</span><hr size=1> &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I was sitting in front of the mirror bushing my hair when Farvak returned to our room.  His face tense with worry over what he and Iszabelle had be arguing about.  How was he going to handle this, how was he going to hide me, protect me.<br>
<br>
 &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  His attention drawn to me as  he started to speak then stopped as he saw that my spell book was beside me. Eyeing me with suspicion and surprise he said &quot; Why are you still here.  You have your book, you could have left at anytime while I was gone.&quot;   <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I stood up and faced him, our bodies touching, my fingers finding the buttons on his shirt. I began unbuttoning them.  My lips found his and passionately, teasingly I kissed him.  Then I whispered &quot;How could I leave you now.  My'lord you are the Love and Master of my life now.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp He stepped back, looking questioningly into my eyes &quot;Kat, what trickery are you up to now&quot;  I let my nails scratch  his chest, cutting into his flesh, I then quickly kissed the wound.  My eyes then found his as I answered seductively &quot;I am sorry  My'Lord, I overheard you as you confessed your love for me to Iszabelle&quot;  Sighing I continued &quot;This is so confusing for me, but then it has all  become so very clear.  You were right Hate and Love are two sides of the same coin.   You have opened my eyes and shown me that&quot;,  I spat with discussed  &quot;Mother Tunare has used me my whole life.  You were right and you are the Truth that has set me free&quot;.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I knelt at his feet and said &quot;Thank you, My'Lord&quot;.  Farvak's eyes gleamed with delight as the thought of his plan for my transformation into his servant and wife seemed close at hand. He pulled me close and  kissed me back.  Hungry he lifted me to carry me to the bed.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Then the moment was broken by the remembrance of Iszabelle's words  &quot;Kill her today.&quot;   He looked at me and said &quot;Kat it is time we go to O'Berton.  Get us there quickly your life depends on it&quot;.   <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Straightening my clothes I picked up my spell book and began to cast.  &quot;I belive you said he was in High Hold Pass. Yes?&quot;   He grinned &quot;You've a mind like a trap&quot;.  He put his strong arms around me  as we were teleported to the Druid Ring in Misty Thicket.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Quickly we moved through Rivervale and Kithicor Forest to the high cliff walls that would lead us to High Hold Pass.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Farvak in the lead now guided me to an older, forgotten part of the Keep.  Once there we were shown to a study and I was told to wait there.  I knew Farvak would be taken to see O'Berton.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  I opened my mind and let all of those that were there enter.  What they would find is a stone cold heart, confusion, and twist of truth that would lead them to believe that I was truly under Farvak's control.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I waited as I felt dark forces all around me closing in.  I knew what I had planned could be suicide.  I could find myself lost in Farvak's dark world, forever mad. Or better for me, at least, be with Caddil and our Child.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp O'Berton would be suspicious of Farvak but would find no trickery in his heart about what he would say about Iszabelle and her failures to bring about the downfall of the Bronze Dragon Fellowship.  He would send for Iszabelle, seeking out answers to why she had failed.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp O'berton's Imp followed him into the study as I turned to face the three of them.  O'berton looked me over and then I felt his mind enter mine looking for any thoughts or emotions that would betray me.  He spoke into my mind &quot;You confess love for Farvak and yet I find none&quot;   I answered &quot;Hate and Love are but emotions. I serve Farvak and if he serves you then so do I&quot;   &quot;What of the Bronze Dragons don't you serve them&quot;.  I thought  &quot;Look deep here you will see that I have Hate for them all now.  For being a caring family they haven't shown it once. For they  sent no one to save Caddil, or me, and let my child die&quot;  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  &quot;Ah&quot;, he said as he searched on. &quot;What of Mother Tunare?&quot; <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp   &quot;Lies all lies, Farvak has shown me that my eyes were closed by lies&quot; I answered bitterly.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Good&quot; He said &quot;Now you will be shown to a room to rest we will talk again later. My Imp Safvas will guard you as I have more to speak of with Farvak&quot;.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The Imp flapped it's batlike wings as we headed down the hall.  It's face was twisted in a grotetesque smile.  &quot;In here white skin&quot; He ordered his voice a gravely high pitched scratch.  He smelled me as I walked past, his nostrils flared.  I walked across the room to the doors that opened out onto a balcony and stood there.  Safvas said &quot;Come back inside. Now!&quot;  I turned and answered &quot;No&quot;.  I smiled at the Imp and said &quot;Have you ever tasted Wood Elf Blood?&quot;     <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Safvas looked and me and licked his lips.  &quot;I have only heard tell.  Some say it is very sweet&quot;.   I offered &quot;would you like to taste mine&quot;  I held out my arm.  This drew the Imp closer.  As he settled closely to me.  I said &quot;Please be gentle&quot;.  He bit down and started sucking up my blood.  So engrossed in his feeding,  he didn't feel me casting a spell on him of Stinging Swarm.  But it wasn't long before, I was quickly becoming dizzy from the lack of blood.  The Imp was delighted and emoting over his meal.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp It was then that Farvak entered the room saw me in distress, drew his blade and killed the Imp.  But not befor the Imp called out to O'Berton &quot;Spy Lord, Spys!&quot;<br>
O'Berton burst into the room as Farvak was lifting me to the bed.  Farvak said threateningly &quot;So you would have killed her while you put me in charge of the Plague Bringers.  This behind my back is this all Iszabelle's plan?&quot;.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp O'Berton looked shocked and then simply waved him off, saying.  &quot;Didn't know Imp's had a weakness for Elven Blood.  Sorry, No harm done, she lives&quot;.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Smiling weakly I looked into Farvak's eyes and said &quot;I will be fine I just need some fruit and rest love.&quot;  He looked at the bite wounds on my arms licked at the last drops and said grinning &quot;I see why the Imp couldn't resist you&quot;  He bandaged my wounds and brushed my hair from my face. While I ate and drank the fruit and wine that O'Berton had ordered brought.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Sometime in the middle of the night I awoke to find Farvak asleep beside me.  It was now that I tried to contact Kygero.  Using the code she had taught me when we first met.  She and I had been laying in wait to kill the leader of the Bandits here in High Hold pass for a valuable page needed for the Testament of Vanear.  She and I didn't want the Bandits over here us or our plans. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  If O'Berton discovered me sending a message it would be easily explained away.  I would simply say that I was discovered here in High Hold Pass by, what use to be, a friend.  I needed to keep the Bronze Dragons complacent.  Letting them know I was safe and why I had not come to them. Explaining that I had be infected by the Plague and refused to endanger my family and not to send a rescue. This expiation would work, I was sure of it.   <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Kygero was here and close.  I told her that the Bronze Dragons had a chance to &quot;Cut the Head Off the Snake&quot; so to speak.  Thereby destroying the Plague Bringers from the head down.  If they moved quickly and secretively they could lay in wait till Iszabelle was here and then attack killing them all.  I would let her know when Iszabelle arrived. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I stood out on the balcony as the sun rose in the ski turning it shades of orange on a blue pallet.  Farvak came up behind me kissing my neck, teasingly biting at my ear lobes.  He said grinning &quot;Come back to bed love I am in the mood for passion and you.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp O'Berton met us in the Dinning area later that day.  He eyed me and again entered my mind &quot;Iszabelle says your pulling Farvak's strings&quot;   I let my mind open up and said back &quot;Not unlike any woman who is smart around Farvak, or any man for that mater.  See for yourself search my mind for your answers&quot;.  This open invitation took O'Berton by surprise.  He turned to Farvak ordered  &quot;Come with me&quot; turned and walked away.   I returned to my room feeling the coldness in the shadows that could only mean one thing &quot;Iszabelle was here&quot;.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I am watching you&quot; she said in my mind, now close and threatening. &quot;You think your safe here?&quot;.  I answered &quot;Safer than you right now&quot;.  I returned to my room.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I sent Kygero one word &quot;Now&quot;.  and waited for the storm that would wash Norrath clean of this Plague once and for all.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp It wasn't long before the Bronze Dragons entered that part of the Keep. They had been gathering in number under Lord Rashek for months and easily out numbered  O'Berton, Farvak and Iszabelle.  They  were soon taken prisoners and the deed done.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Everything seemed anticlimactic as if there was something missing. <br>
  <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp It wasn't till later when Kygero explained what had been going on with the Guild that my heart was again broken.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  It seemed that the Guild had suffered its own losses in my absence.  An internal struggle had occurred ending with Lady Molina leaving and heading out with Lady Kelee and Phyllis at her side to help find the cure that would heal Khaldron who was still very ill.  Lord Rashek now had more duties as he was given Regency Over the guild we now had a new High Lord.  High Lord Tiggyr and his new wife High Lady Bekkaha who was with child now. There were many new faces in court as well as some old dear friends.  Regency High Lord Rashek had appointed me as an officer and I was welcomed into the court by High Lord Tiggyr with honor.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I requested that I be given leave from my duties as I needed to renew my faith with Mother Tunare and erase the doubts and mistrust that Farvak had planted.  My heart now had time to grieve deeply for Caddil and our lost Child.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp It was on just one of these nights when I lay in bed letting the grief take over like a sea at high tide, that Mother Tunare came to me again.  She said that Caddil's spirit had survived.  That he was now a young mage.  However all memories of me were gone.  To try and remind him of our love and life would only drive him mad. That this  was the work of the Gods as they had need of his spirit in the future of Norrath. <p>One Very Adventurous Druid<BR>Katreena Wanderheart 41nd Leaf Master Brewer <BR>
